---
import ProductLayout from "@layouts/ProductLayout.astro";
---

<ProductLayout
  title="ADHD Career Change Workbook | ClearCareer"
  description="A complete career change system designed for how ADHD brains actually work."
  headline="Career change is hard.<br />Career change with ADHD is<br />a whole different challenge."
  subheadline="Built by someone with ADHD. 6 guides that replace impulsive pivots with a framework your brain can actually follow. Interest vs. fixation filters, dopamine career mapping, and 2-week sprint plans instead of 90-day goals that never happen."
  bullets={[
    "Decision framework: Is it ADHD or is the job actually wrong?",
    "Dopamine career map: careers matched to ADHD strengths",
    "Transferable skills translator for scattered experience",
    "Financial runway calculator with ADHD-friendly budgeting",
    "2-week sprint model (because 90-day plans fail ADHD brains)",
    "How to tell your career story without sounding 'scattered'",
  ]}
  price="$24 CAD"
  ctaHref="#checkout"
  ctaText="Get Instant Access"
  guaranteeText="30-day money-back guarantee. No questions asked."
  faq={[
    {
      q: "I'm not sure if I need a career change or just a new job. Will this help?",
      a: "Guide 1 is specifically about answering that question. It includes an 'interest vs. fixation' filter to help you tell the difference between ADHD boredom and genuine misalignment.",
    },
    {
      q: "How is this different from the ADHD Focus Kit?",
      a: "The Focus Kit helps you search for any job with ADHD. This workbook is specifically for changing careers, with tools for exploring new paths, translating skills, and making the financial math work.",
    },
    {
      q: "Do I need a diagnosis to use this?",
      a: "No. If you struggle with impulsive decisions, difficulty sustaining interest, or executive function challenges when planning big life changes, these frameworks will help.",
    },
    {
      q: "What about the financial side? I can't just quit.",
      a: "Guide 4 covers financial runway in detail: minimum viable income calculations, the parallel track approach (don't quit until the new thing pays), and ADHD-friendly budget tracking.",
    },
    {
      q: "Should I disclose ADHD in interviews for my new career?",
      a: "Guide 6 includes a disclosure decision framework. Short answer: it depends on the role, company, and your comfort level. The framework walks you through the pros, cons, and how to make the call.",
    },
  ]}
/>
